00:57:35.250 --> 00:57:39.910 position:56%
I'd like to know what can be done
politically, men and women together,

00:57:39.910 --> 00:57:44.110
to bring about the creation of
a Cabinet secretary of culture.

00:57:44.110 --> 00:57:48.570
Hungary, since time in [inaudible]
has had a Minister of Culture.

00:57:48.570 --> 00:57:51.580
France has had, Greece has had.

00:57:51.580 --> 00:57:54.590
It's indefensible that we do not.

00:57:55.630 --> 00:58:00.290
&gt;&gt; Jane Chu: Why are
you looking at me?

00:58:00.290 --> 00:58:03.210
&gt;&gt; Margaret Lioi: Well - oh, here.

00:58:03.210 --> 00:58:05.860 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Annette McLean: I think just I'll
start out by just referring again

00:58:05.860 --> 00:58:09.610
to the wonderful comment that
we were talking about earlier,

00:58:09.610 --> 00:58:13.340
Mrs. Coolidge said, we have
a secretary of hygiene,

00:58:13.340 --> 00:58:15.810
one of education, and
one of welfare,

00:58:15.810 --> 00:58:18.360
but we do not have a
secretary of fine arts.

00:58:18.360 --> 00:58:21.970
In fact, to have Jane
Chu is pretty amazing.

00:58:21.970 --> 00:58:23.460
You're right that we
need to move forward,

00:58:23.460 --> 00:58:25.520
and I'll let you speak to that.

00:58:25.520 --> 00:58:32.920
&gt;&gt; Margaret Lioi: Well, I -- that's
actually a very controversial idea,

00:58:32.920 --> 00:58:38.140
and there are many, many people
who are not in favor of it.

00:58:38.140 --> 00:58:45.810 position:56%
Not because -- because when you have
a cultural minister that also leads

00:58:45.810 --> 00:58:49.590
to other kinds of issues
that we don't have to deal

00:58:49.590 --> 00:58:51.440
with here in the United States.

00:58:51.440 --> 00:58:53.620
I think that actually the --

00:58:53.620 --> 00:59:01.060
having an agency the way
that we do is actually --

00:59:01.060 --> 00:59:05.120
I think some of the European
countries look to the United States

00:59:05.120 --> 00:59:11.960
to see how robust our philanthropy
is, which is based a great deal

00:59:11.960 --> 00:59:14.220
on the presence of the
National Endowment,

00:59:14.220 --> 00:59:18.780
and how it's grants leverage
money from the private sector.

00:59:18.780 --> 00:59:23.050 position:56%
That doesn't happen in the same way
when you have a Minister of Culture.

00:59:23.050 --> 00:59:25.780
So I understand people's --

00:59:25.780 --> 00:59:30.460
the impetus of we need somebody
there that's just for culture,

00:59:30.460 --> 00:59:34.980
but there are other
consequences of having that system

00:59:34.980 --> 00:59:36.690
that we don't have in this country.

00:59:36.690 --> 00:59:39.650
And so I'm not so much
in favor of --

00:59:39.650 --> 00:59:44.220 position:56%
I'm in favor of Jane Chu [laughter].

00:59:44.220 --> 00:59:46.090
I think she should do it.

